'''Aleksandr Iosifovich Popov''' ({{lang-ru|Александр Иосифович Попов}}; 7&nbsp;June 1913 in [[Tartu|Dorpat]], [[Governorate of Livonia]], [[Russian Empire]] – 23 April 1993 in [[Moscow]], [[Russia]])<ref name=msu/> was a [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[permafrost]] researcher at the [[Moscow State University]]. He served as head of the Department of Cryolithology and Glaciology.<ref>General Geocryology, p. 24</ref> Popov was a member of the International Commission on [[periglaciation|Periglacial Morphology]] of the [[International Geographical Union]]. He organized and led numerous expeditions to investigate permafrost and deep seasonal freezing in the Soviet Union.<ref name=msu>[http://www.geogr.msu.ru/about/rank/element.php?IBLOCK_ID=4&SECTION_ID=0&ELEMENT_ID=868 Попов А.И. Заслуженный деятель науки РСФСР (1988)]</ref> Popov edited the [[geocryological]] map of the Soviet Union that was published in 1986.<ref>General Geocryology, p. 489</ref>
