{{self-published|date=November 2015}} {{Infobox Website | name = HerpMapper | logo = HerpMapper_Logo_v2_non-free.png | logo_size = 150px | screenshot = | caption = | url = {{URL|http://www.herpmapper.org}} | slogan = | commercial = No | type = [[Citizen science]] | language = English | registration = required | author = | launch date = {{Start date and age|2013|df=yes|br=yes}} | current status = Online }}
'''HerpMapper''' is a cooperative [[citizen science]] project designed to gather and share information about [[reptile]] and [[amphibian]] (herp) observations across the planet.<ref name='tncblog'>{{cite web|title=Record Your Reptile & Amphibian Sightings for Conservation|url=http://blog.nature.org/science/2016/03/22/record-your-reptile-amphibian-sightings-for-conservation//|date=22 March 2016|accessdate=14 May 2016}}</ref> Contributors create records of their herp observations [[online]]<ref name='onlineinstructs'>{{cite web|title=Instructions|url=http://www.herpmapper.org/help|date=22 December 2014|accessdate=22 December 2014}}</ref> or via its [[mobile application]].<ref name='googleapp'>{{cite web|title=Mobile Mapper application (Google Play)|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=org.herpmapper.MobileMapper|date=17 December 2014|accessdate=22 December 2014}}</ref><ref name='appleapp'>{{cite web|title=Mobile Mapper application (iTunes Store)|url=https://itunes.apple.com/app/id670772103|date=11 July 2014|accessdate=22 December 2014}}</ref><ref name='windowsapp'>{{cite web|title=Mobile Mapper application (Windows Store)|url=https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/store/apps/mobile-mapper/9nblggh0mk0g|date=2 February 2016|accessdate=2 February 2016}}</ref> Data are available to HerpMapper [[Business partner|Partners]] – groups who use your recorded observations for [[research]], [[conservation biology|conservation]], and [[Conservation (ethic)|preservation]] purposes.<ref name='partners'>{{cite web|title=Partners|url=http://www.herpmapper.org/partners|date=22 December 2014|accessdate=22 December 2014}}</ref><ref name='monitoring1'>{{cite web|title=Twin Cities Turtle Crossing Tally and Count|url=http://www.herpmapper.org/content/pdf/mn-turtles-and-roads-project.pdf|date=1 March 2016|accessdate=14 May 2016}}</ref><ref name='monitoring2'>{{cite web|title=Helping turtles across the street|url=http://www.startribune.com/local/east/265922831.html|date=5 July 2014|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref><ref name='monitoring3'>{{cite web|title=WCD - Conservation Connections|url=http://static.squarespace.com/static/5201a163e4b01f15d7f763c6/t/547dcad3e4b0f4bc27e09489/1417530067326/WCD+News_Final_11-2014.pdf|date=November 2014|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> In addition, the HerpMapper [[mobile application]] is used by multiple other herpetological atlas projects,<ref name='HERP'>{{cite web|title=H.E.R.P.|url=http://www.naherp.com/|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref><ref name='MIHerpAtlas'>{{cite web|title=Michigan Herp Atlas|url=http://www.miherpatlas.org/|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref><ref name='PAHerpAtlas'>{{cite web|title=Pennsylvania Amphibian and Reptile Survey|url=http://www.paherpsurvey.org/|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> and the Minnesota Nongame Wildlife Program.<ref name='MNNWP'>{{cite web|title=Minnesota Nongame Wildlife Program|url=http://www.mndnr.gov/nongame|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref>
HerpMapper's primary goal is to share data with professional conservation and research organizations to better conserve [[herpetofauna]] around the world. Because of this, HerpMapper does not share point-location information publicly because of over-collection and [[poaching]] concerns. This sets HerpMapper apart from many other citizen-science projects.
== History == [http://www.herpmapper.org/ HerpMapper.org] was officially launched in September 2013. It is currently a volunteer-run organization of professional herpetologists, IT specialists, and field herpers with decades of experience. HerpMapper is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization.
== Organizational Structure == The HerpMapper Advisory Team includes nonprofit organization staff, state agency [[biologists]], university faculty, [[Information technology|IT]] professionals, and field [[herpers]] with decades of experience. Learn more on the [http://www.herpmapper.org/about About Us] webpage.
== Data Access == Data are made freely available to professional conservation and research organizations. Data are made available via real-time online access or via one-time data transfers.
