In the field of [[physical chemistry]], a nonthermal surface reaction refers to an elementary reaction between a thermally accommodated adsorbed surface species and a reactant which has not yet thermally accommodated to the surface.
The two main mechanisms classified as nonthermal are the [[Reactions on surfaces|Eley-Rideal]] and [[hot atom]] mediated mechanisms.

{{DEFAULTSORT:Nonthermal Surface Reaction}}
[[Category:Surface science]]


{{physical-chemistry-stub}}

'''Raster Navigational Charts''' (RNC's) are created by the [[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration]] (NOAA) of the United States Government. Each original chart is scanned at high resolution with color separate overlays. The [[raster graphics|raster]] file also contains data that is Geo-referencing; enabling computer based navigation attached to a [[GPS]] to locate and display the chart.
The charts are stored in BSB {{clarify|date=July 2013}} format. Image manipulation tools such as [[GDAL]] can read the image information, but there also is georeferenced data in the navigational charts.
==See also== *[[Electronic navigational chart]]
