{{ic|date=January 2018}}The structured computer-aided logic design ('''SCALD''') software, was a computer aided design system developed for building the S-1 computer. It used the [[Stanford University]] Drawing System (SUDS), and it was developed by Thomas M. McWilliams and Lawrence Curtis Widdoes, Jr. The work led to the start of the [[Valid Logic Systems]] company.

